40rtc::PacketInfoProtocolType ConvertProtocolTypeToPacketInfoProtocolType(
41 cricket::ProtocolType type) {
42 switch (type) {
43 case cricket::ProtocolType::PROTO_UDP:
44 return rtc::PacketInfoProtocolType::kUdp;
45 case cricket::ProtocolType::PROTO_TCP:
46 return rtc::PacketInfoProtocolType::kTcp;
47 case cricket::ProtocolType::PROTO_SSLTCP:
48 return rtc::PacketInfoProtocolType::kSsltcp;
49 case cricket::ProtocolType::PROTO_TLS:
50 return rtc::PacketInfoProtocolType::kTls;
51 default:
52 return rtc::PacketInfoProtocolType::kUnknown;
53 }
54}

56// The delay before we begin checking if this port is useless. We set
57// it to a little higher than a total STUN timeout.
58const int kPortTimeoutDelay = cricket::STUN_TOTAL_TIMEOUT + 5000;

67// TODO(ronghuawu): Use "local", "srflx", "prflx" and "relay". But this requires
68// the signaling part be updated correspondingly as well.
69const char LOCAL_PORT_TYPE[] = "local";
70const char STUN_PORT_TYPE[] = "stun";
71const char PRFLX_PORT_TYPE[] = "prflx";
72const char RELAY_PORT_TYPE[] = "relay";
73
74static const char* const PROTO_NAMES[] = {UDP_PROTOCOL_NAME, TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME,
75 SSLTCP_PROTOCOL_NAME,
76 TLS_PROTOCOL_NAME};
77
78const char* ProtoToString(ProtocolType proto) {
79 return PROTO_NAMES[proto];
80}
81
82bool StringToProto(const char* value, ProtocolType* proto) {
83 for (size_t i = 0; i <= PROTO_LAST; ++i) {
84 if (absl::EqualsIgnoreCase(PROTO_NAMES[i], value)) {
85 *proto = static_cast<ProtocolType>(i);
86 return true;
87 }
88 }
89 return false;
90}

92// RFC 6544, TCP candidate encoding rules.
93const int DISCARD_PORT = 9;
94const char TCPTYPE_ACTIVE_STR[] = "active";
95const char TCPTYPE_PASSIVE_STR[] = "passive";
96const char TCPTYPE_SIMOPEN_STR[] = "so";

98std::string Port::ComputeFoundation(const std::string& type,
99 const std::string& protocol,
100 const std::string& relay_protocol,
101 const rtc::SocketAddress& base_address) {
102 rtc::StringBuilder sb;
103 sb << type << base_address.ipaddr().ToString() << protocol << relay_protocol;
104 return rtc::ToString(rtc::ComputeCrc32(sb.Release()));
105}

173void Port::Construct() {
174 // TODO(pthatcher): Remove this old behavior once we're sure no one
175 // relies on it. If the username_fragment and password are empty,
176 // we should just create one.
177 if (ice_username_fragment_.empty()) {
178 RTC_DCHECK(password_.empty());
179 ice_username_fragment_ = rtc::CreateRandomString(ICE_UFRAG_LENGTH);
180 password_ = rtc::CreateRandomString(ICE_PWD_LENGTH);
181 }
182 network_->SignalTypeChanged.connect(this, &Port::OnNetworkTypeChanged);
183 network_cost_ = network_->GetCost();
184
185 thread_->PostDelayed(RTC_FROM_HERE, timeout_delay_, this,
186 MSG_DESTROY_IF_DEAD);
187 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Port created with network cost "
188 << network_cost_;
189}
190
191Port::~Port() {
192 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
193 CancelPendingTasks();
194
195 // Delete all of the remaining connections. We copy the list up front
196 // because each deletion will cause it to be modified.
197
198 std::vector<Connection*> list;
199
200 AddressMap::iterator iter = connections_.begin();
201 while (iter != connections_.end()) {
202 list.push_back(iter->second);
203 ++iter;
204 }
205
206 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < list.size(); i++)
207 delete list[i];
208}

236void Port::SetIceParameters(int component,
237 const std::string& username_fragment,
238 const std::string& password) {
239 component_ = component;
240 ice_username_fragment_ = username_fragment;
241 password_ = password;
242 for (Candidate& c : candidates_) {

244 c.set_username(username_fragment);

261void Port::AddAddress(const rtc::SocketAddress& address,
262 const rtc::SocketAddress& base_address,
263 const rtc::SocketAddress& related_address,
264 const std::string& protocol,
265 const std::string& relay_protocol,
266 const std::string& tcptype,
267 const std::string& type,
268 uint32_t type_preference,
269 uint32_t relay_preference,
270 const std::string& url,
271 bool is_final) {
272 if (protocol == TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME && type == LOCAL_PORT_TYPE) {
273 RTC_DCHECK(!tcptype.empty());
274 }
275
276 std::string foundation =
277 ComputeFoundation(type, protocol, relay_protocol, base_address);
278 Candidate c(component_, protocol, address, 0U, username_fragment(), password_,
279 type, generation_, foundation, network_->id(), network_cost_);
280 c.set_priority(
281 c.GetPriority(type_preference, network_->preference(), relay_preference));
282 c.set_relay_protocol(relay_protocol);
283 c.set_tcptype(tcptype);
284 c.set_network_name(network_->name());
285 c.set_network_type(network_->type());
286 c.set_url(url);
287 c.set_related_address(related_address);
288
289 bool pending = MaybeObfuscateAddress(&c, type, is_final);
290
291 if (!pending) {
292 FinishAddingAddress(c, is_final);
293 }
294}
295
296bool Port::MaybeObfuscateAddress(Candidate* c,
297 const std::string& type,
298 bool is_final) {
299 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/9723): Use a config to control the feature of IP
300 // handling with mDNS.
301 if (network_->GetMdnsResponder() == nullptr) {
302 return false;
303 }
304 if (type != LOCAL_PORT_TYPE) {
305 return false;
306 }
307
308 auto copy = *c;
309 auto weak_ptr = weak_factory_.GetWeakPtr();
310 auto callback = [weak_ptr, copy, is_final](const rtc::IPAddress& addr,
311 const std::string& name) mutable {
312 RTC_DCHECK(copy.address().ipaddr() == addr);
313 rtc::SocketAddress hostname_address(name, copy.address().port());
314 // In Port and Connection, we need the IP address information to
315 // correctly handle the update of candidate type to prflx. The removal
316 // of IP address when signaling this candidate will take place in
317 // BasicPortAllocatorSession::OnCandidateReady, via SanitizeCandidate.
318 hostname_address.SetResolvedIP(addr);
319 copy.set_address(hostname_address);
320 copy.set_related_address(rtc::SocketAddress());
321 if (weak_ptr != nullptr) {
322 weak_ptr->set_mdns_name_registration_status(
323 MdnsNameRegistrationStatus::kCompleted);
324 weak_ptr->FinishAddingAddress(copy, is_final);
325 }
326 };
327 set_mdns_name_registration_status(MdnsNameRegistrationStatus::kInProgress);
328 network_->GetMdnsResponder()->CreateNameForAddress(copy.address().ipaddr(),
329 callback);
330 return true;
331}
332
333void Port::FinishAddingAddress(const Candidate& c, bool is_final) {
334 candidates_.push_back(c);
335 SignalCandidateReady(this, c);
336
337 PostAddAddress(is_final);
338}
339
340void Port::PostAddAddress(bool is_final) {
341 if (is_final) {
342 SignalPortComplete(this);
343 }
344}
345
346void Port::AddOrReplaceConnection(Connection* conn) {
347 auto ret = connections_.insert(
348 std::make_pair(conn->remote_candidate().address(), conn));
349 // If there is a different connection on the same remote address, replace
350 // it with the new one and destroy the old one.
351 if (ret.second == false && ret.first->second != conn) {
352 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
353 << ToString()
354 << ": A new connection was created on an existing remote address. "
355 "New remote candidate: "
356 << conn->remote_candidate().ToSensitiveString();
357 ret.first->second->SignalDestroyed.disconnect(this);
358 ret.first->second->Destroy();
359 ret.first->second = conn;
360 }
361 conn->SignalDestroyed.connect(this, &Port::OnConnectionDestroyed);
362 SignalConnectionCreated(this, conn);
363}
364
365void Port::OnReadPacket(const char* data,
366 size_t size,
367 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
368 ProtocolType proto) {
369 // If the user has enabled port packets, just hand this over.
370 if (enable_port_packets_) {
371 SignalReadPacket(this, data, size, addr);
372 return;
373 }
374
375 // If this is an authenticated STUN request, then signal unknown address and
376 // send back a proper binding response.
377 std::unique_ptr<IceMessage> msg;
378 std::string remote_username;
379 if (!GetStunMessage(data, size, addr, &msg, &remote_username)) {
380 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
381 << ": Received non-STUN packet from unknown address: "
382 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
383 } else if (!msg) {
384 // STUN message handled already
385 } else if (msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
386 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Received " << StunMethodToString(msg->type())
387 << " id=" << rtc::hex_encode(msg->transaction_id())
388 << " from unknown address " << addr.ToSensitiveString();
389 // We need to signal an unknown address before we handle any role conflict
390 // below. Otherwise there would be no candidate pair and TURN entry created
391 // to send the error response in case of a role conflict.
392 SignalUnknownAddress(this, addr, proto, msg.get(), remote_username, false);
393 // Check for role conflicts.
394 if (!MaybeIceRoleConflict(addr, msg.get(), remote_username)) {
395 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Received conflicting role from the peer.";
396 return;
397 }
398 } else if (msg->type() == GOOG_PING_REQUEST) {
399 // This is a PING sent to a connection that was destroyed.
400 // Send back that this is the case and a authenticated BINDING
401 // is needed.
402 SendBindingErrorResponse(msg.get(), addr, STUN_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST,
403 STUN_ERROR_REASON_BAD_REQUEST);
404 } else {
405 // NOTE(tschmelcher): STUN_BINDING_RESPONSE is benign. It occurs if we
406 // pruned a connection for this port while it had STUN requests in flight,
407 // because we then get back responses for them, which this code correctly
408 // does not handle.
409 if (msg->type() != STUN_BINDING_RESPONSE &&
410 msg->type() != GOOG_PING_RESPONSE &&
411 msg->type() != GOOG_PING_ERROR_RESPONSE) {
412 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
413 << ": Received unexpected STUN message type: "
414 << msg->type() << " from unknown address: "
415 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
416 }
417 }
418}

420void Port::OnReadyToSend() {
421 AddressMap::iterator iter = connections_.begin();
422 for (; iter != connections_.end(); ++iter) {
423 iter->second->OnReadyToSend();
424 }

432bool Port::GetStunMessage(const char* data,
433 size_t size,
434 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
435 std::unique_ptr<IceMessage>* out_msg,
436 std::string* out_username) {
437 // NOTE: This could clearly be optimized to avoid allocating any memory.
438 // However, at the data rates we'll be looking at on the client side,
439 // this probably isn't worth worrying about.
440 RTC_DCHECK(out_msg != NULL);
441 RTC_DCHECK(out_username != NULL);
442 out_username->clear();
443
444 // Don't bother parsing the packet if we can tell it's not STUN.
445 // In ICE mode, all STUN packets will have a valid fingerprint.
446 // Except GOOG_PING_REQUEST/RESPONSE that does not send fingerprint.
447 int types[] = {GOOG_PING_REQUEST, GOOG_PING_RESPONSE,
448 GOOG_PING_ERROR_RESPONSE};
449 if (!StunMessage::IsStunMethod(types, data, size) &&
450 !StunMessage::ValidateFingerprint(data, size)) {
451 return false;
452 }
453
454 // Parse the request message. If the packet is not a complete and correct
455 // STUN message, then ignore it.
456 std::unique_ptr<IceMessage> stun_msg(new IceMessage());
457 rtc::ByteBufferReader buf(data, size);
458 if (!stun_msg->Read(&buf) || (buf.Length() > 0)) {
459 return false;
460 }
461
462 // Get list of attributes in the "comprehension-required" range that were not
463 // comprehended. If one or more is found, the behavior differs based on the
464 // type of the incoming message; see below.
465 std::vector<uint16_t> unknown_attributes =
466 stun_msg->GetNonComprehendedAttributes();
467
468 if (stun_msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
469 // Check for the presence of USERNAME and MESSAGE-INTEGRITY (if ICE) first.
470 // If not present, fail with a 400 Bad Request.
471 if (!stun_msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME) ||
472 !stun_msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_MESSAGE_INTEGRITY)) {
473 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Received "
474 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type())
475 << " without username/M-I from: "
476 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
477 SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg.get(), addr, STUN_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST,
478 STUN_ERROR_REASON_BAD_REQUEST);
479 return true;
480 }
481
482 // If the username is bad or unknown, fail with a 401 Unauthorized.
483 std::string local_ufrag;
484 std::string remote_ufrag;
485 if (!ParseStunUsername(stun_msg.get(), &local_ufrag, &remote_ufrag) ||
486 local_ufrag != username_fragment()) {
487 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Received "
488 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type())
489 << " with bad local username " << local_ufrag
490 << " from " << addr.ToSensitiveString();
491 SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg.get(), addr, STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED,
492 STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNAUTHORIZED);
493 return true;
494 }
495
496 // If ICE, and the MESSAGE-INTEGRITY is bad, fail with a 401 Unauthorized
497 if (stun_msg->ValidateMessageIntegrity(password_) !=
498 StunMessage::IntegrityStatus::kIntegrityOk) {
499 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Received "
500 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type())
501 << " with bad M-I from " << addr.ToSensitiveString()
502 << ", password_=" << password_;
503 SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg.get(), addr, STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED,
504 STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNAUTHORIZED);
505 return true;
506 }
507
508 // If a request contains unknown comprehension-required attributes, reply
509 // with an error. See RFC5389 section 7.3.1.
510 if (!unknown_attributes.empty()) {
511 SendUnknownAttributesErrorResponse(stun_msg.get(), addr,
512 unknown_attributes);
513 return true;
514 }
515
516 out_username->assign(remote_ufrag);
517 } else if ((stun_msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_RESPONSE) ||
518 (stun_msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_ERROR_RESPONSE)) {
519 if (stun_msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_ERROR_RESPONSE) {
520 if (const StunErrorCodeAttribute* error_code = stun_msg->GetErrorCode()) {
521 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Received "
522 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type())
523 << ": class=" << error_code->eclass()
524 << " number=" << error_code->number() << " reason='"
525 << error_code->reason() << "' from "
526 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
527 // Return message to allow error-specific processing
528 } else {
529 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Received "
530 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type())
531 << " without a error code from "
532 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
533 return true;
534 }
535 }
536 // If a response contains unknown comprehension-required attributes, it's
537 // simply discarded and the transaction is considered failed. See RFC5389
538 // sections 7.3.3 and 7.3.4.
539 if (!unknown_attributes.empty()) {
540 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
541 << ": Discarding STUN response due to unknown "
542 "comprehension-required attribute";
543 return true;
544 }
545 // NOTE: Username should not be used in verifying response messages.
546 out_username->clear();
547 } else if (stun_msg->type() == STUN_BINDING_INDICATION) {
548 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": Received "
549 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type()) << ": from "
550 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
551 out_username->clear();
552
553 // If an indication contains unknown comprehension-required attributes,[]
554 // it's simply discarded. See RFC5389 section 7.3.2.
555 if (!unknown_attributes.empty()) {
556 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
557 << ": Discarding STUN indication due to "
558 "unknown comprehension-required attribute";
559 return true;
560 }
561 // No stun attributes will be verified, if it's stun indication message.
562 // Returning from end of the this method.
563 } else if (stun_msg->type() == GOOG_PING_REQUEST) {
564 if (stun_msg->ValidateMessageIntegrity(password_) !=
565 StunMessage::IntegrityStatus::kIntegrityOk) {
566 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Received "
567 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type())
568 << " with bad M-I from " << addr.ToSensitiveString()
569 << ", password_=" << password_;
570 SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg.get(), addr, STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED,
571 STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNAUTHORIZED);
572 return true;
573 }
574 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": Received "
575 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type()) << " from "
576 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
577 out_username->clear();
578 } else if (stun_msg->type() == GOOG_PING_RESPONSE ||
579 stun_msg->type() == GOOG_PING_ERROR_RESPONSE) {
580 // note: the MessageIntegrity32 will be verified in Connection.cc
581 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE) << ToString() << ": Received "
582 << StunMethodToString(stun_msg->type()) << " from "
583 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
584 out_username->clear();
585 } else {
586 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString()
587 << ": Received STUN packet with invalid type ("
588 << stun_msg->type() << ") from "
589 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
590 return true;
591 }
592
593 // Return the STUN message found.
594 *out_msg = std::move(stun_msg);
595 return true;
596}
597
598bool Port::IsCompatibleAddress(const rtc::SocketAddress& addr) {
599 // Get a representative IP for the Network this port is configured to use.
600 rtc::IPAddress ip = network_->GetBestIP();
601 // We use single-stack sockets, so families must match.
602 if (addr.family() != ip.family()) {
603 return false;
604 }
605 // Link-local IPv6 ports can only connect to other link-local IPv6 ports.
606 if (ip.family() == AF_INET6 &&
607 (IPIsLinkLocal(ip) != IPIsLinkLocal(addr.ipaddr()))) {
608 return false;
609 }
610 return true;
611}

615 return rtc::DSCP_NO_CHANGE;

618void Port::set_timeout_delay(int delay) {
619 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
620 // Although this method is meant to only be used by tests, some downstream
621 // projects have started using it. Ideally we should update our tests to not
622 // require to modify this state and instead use a testing harness that allows
623 // adjusting the clock and then just use the kPortTimeoutDelay constant
624 // directly.
625 timeout_delay_ = delay;
626}
627
628bool Port::ParseStunUsername(const StunMessage* stun_msg,
629 std::string* local_ufrag,
630 std::string* remote_ufrag) const {
631 // The packet must include a username that either begins or ends with our
632 // fragment. It should begin with our fragment if it is a request and it
633 // should end with our fragment if it is a response.
634 local_ufrag->clear();
635 remote_ufrag->clear();
636 const StunByteStringAttribute* username_attr =
637 stun_msg->GetByteString(STUN_ATTR_USERNAME);
638 if (username_attr == NULL)
639 return false;
640
641 // RFRAG:LFRAG
642 const std::string username = username_attr->GetString();
643 size_t colon_pos = username.find(':');
644 if (colon_pos == std::string::npos) {
645 return false;
646 }
647
648 *local_ufrag = username.substr(0, colon_pos);
649 *remote_ufrag = username.substr(colon_pos + 1, username.size());
650 return true;
651}
652
653bool Port::MaybeIceRoleConflict(const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
654 IceMessage* stun_msg,
655 const std::string& remote_ufrag) {
656 // Validate ICE_CONTROLLING or ICE_CONTROLLED attributes.
657 bool ret = true;
658 IceRole remote_ice_role = ICEROLE_UNKNOWN;
659 uint64_t remote_tiebreaker = 0;
660 const StunUInt64Attribute* stun_attr =
661 stun_msg->GetUInt64(STUN_ATTR_ICE_CONTROLLING);
662 if (stun_attr) {
663 remote_ice_role = ICEROLE_CONTROLLING;
664 remote_tiebreaker = stun_attr->value();
665 }
666
667 // If |remote_ufrag| is same as port local username fragment and
668 // tie breaker value received in the ping message matches port
669 // tiebreaker value this must be a loopback call.
670 // We will treat this as valid scenario.
671 if (remote_ice_role == ICEROLE_CONTROLLING &&
672 username_fragment() == remote_ufrag &&
673 remote_tiebreaker == IceTiebreaker()) {
674 return true;
675 }
676
677 stun_attr = stun_msg->GetUInt64(STUN_ATTR_ICE_CONTROLLED);
678 if (stun_attr) {
679 remote_ice_role = ICEROLE_CONTROLLED;
680 remote_tiebreaker = stun_attr->value();
681 }
682
683 switch (ice_role_) {
684 case ICEROLE_CONTROLLING:
685 if (ICEROLE_CONTROLLING == remote_ice_role) {
686 if (remote_tiebreaker >= tiebreaker_) {
687 SignalRoleConflict(this);
688 } else {
689 // Send Role Conflict (487) error response.
690 SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg, addr, STUN_ERROR_ROLE_CONFLICT,
691 STUN_ERROR_REASON_ROLE_CONFLICT);
692 ret = false;
693 }
694 }
695 break;
696 case ICEROLE_CONTROLLED:
697 if (ICEROLE_CONTROLLED == remote_ice_role) {
698 if (remote_tiebreaker < tiebreaker_) {
699 SignalRoleConflict(this);
700 } else {
701 // Send Role Conflict (487) error response.
702 SendBindingErrorResponse(stun_msg, addr, STUN_ERROR_ROLE_CONFLICT,
703 STUN_ERROR_REASON_ROLE_CONFLICT);
704 ret = false;
705 }
706 }
707 break;
708 default:
709 RTC_NOTREACHED();
710 }
711 return ret;
712}

734
735void Port::SendBindingErrorResponse(StunMessage* request,
736 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
737 int error_code,
738 const std::string& reason) {
739 RTC_DCHECK(request->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST ||
740 request->type() == GOOG_PING_REQUEST);
741
742 // Fill in the response message.
743 StunMessage response;
744 if (request->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
745 response.SetType(STUN_BINDING_ERROR_RESPONSE);
746 } else {
747 response.SetType(GOOG_PING_ERROR_RESPONSE);
748 }
749 response.SetTransactionID(request->transaction_id());
750
751 // When doing GICE, we need to write out the error code incorrectly to
752 // maintain backwards compatiblility.
753 auto error_attr = StunAttribute::CreateErrorCode();
754 error_attr->SetCode(error_code);
755 error_attr->SetReason(reason);
756 response.AddAttribute(std::move(error_attr));
757
758 // Per Section 10.1.2, certain error cases don't get a MESSAGE-INTEGRITY,
759 // because we don't have enough information to determine the shared secret.
760 if (error_code != STUN_ERROR_BAD_REQUEST &&
761 error_code != STUN_ERROR_UNAUTHORIZED &&
762 request->type() != GOOG_PING_REQUEST) {
763 if (request->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
764 response.AddMessageIntegrity(password_);
765 } else {
766 response.AddMessageIntegrity32(password_);
767 }
768 }
769
770 if (request->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST) {
771 response.AddFingerprint();
772 }
773
774 // Send the response message.
775 rtc::ByteBufferWriter buf;
776 response.Write(&buf);
777 rtc::PacketOptions options(StunDscpValue());
778 options.info_signaled_after_sent.packet_type =
779 rtc::PacketType::kIceConnectivityCheckResponse;
780 SendTo(buf.Data(), buf.Length(), addr, options, false);
781 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Sending STUN "
782 << StunMethodToString(response.type())
783 << ": reason=" << reason << " to "
784 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
785}
786
787void Port::SendUnknownAttributesErrorResponse(
788 StunMessage* request,
789 const rtc::SocketAddress& addr,
790 const std::vector<uint16_t>& unknown_types) {
791 RTC_DCHECK(request->type() == STUN_BINDING_REQUEST);
792
793 // Fill in the response message.
794 StunMessage response;
795 response.SetType(STUN_BINDING_ERROR_RESPONSE);
796 response.SetTransactionID(request->transaction_id());
797
798 auto error_attr = StunAttribute::CreateErrorCode();
799 error_attr->SetCode(STUN_ERROR_UNKNOWN_ATTRIBUTE);
800 error_attr->SetReason(STUN_ERROR_REASON_UNKNOWN_ATTRIBUTE);
801 response.AddAttribute(std::move(error_attr));
802
803 std::unique_ptr<StunUInt16ListAttribute> unknown_attr =
804 StunAttribute::CreateUnknownAttributes();
805 for (uint16_t type : unknown_types) {
806 unknown_attr->AddType(type);
807 }
808 response.AddAttribute(std::move(unknown_attr));
809
810 response.AddMessageIntegrity(password_);
811 response.AddFingerprint();
812
813 // Send the response message.
814 rtc::ByteBufferWriter buf;
815 response.Write(&buf);
816 rtc::PacketOptions options(StunDscpValue());
817 options.info_signaled_after_sent.packet_type =
818 rtc::PacketType::kIceConnectivityCheckResponse;
819 SendTo(buf.Data(), buf.Length(), addr, options, false);
820 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << ToString() << ": Sending STUN binding error: reason="
821 << STUN_ERROR_UNKNOWN_ATTRIBUTE << " to "
822 << addr.ToSensitiveString();
823}

825void Port::KeepAliveUntilPruned() {
826 // If it is pruned, we won't bring it up again.
827 if (state_ == State::INIT) {
828 state_ = State::KEEP_ALIVE_UNTIL_PRUNED;
829 }
830}
831
832void Port::Prune() {
833 state_ = State::PRUNED;
834 thread_->Post(RTC_FROM_HERE, this, MSG_DESTROY_IF_DEAD);
835}

837// Call to stop any currently pending operations from running.
838void Port::CancelPendingTasks() {
839 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
840 thread_->Clear(this);
841}
842
843void Port::OnMessage(rtc::Message* pmsg) {
844 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(thread_);
845 RTC_DCHECK(pmsg->message_id == MSG_DESTROY_IF_DEAD);
846 bool dead =
847 (state_ == State::INIT || state_ == State::PRUNED) &&
848 connections_.empty() &&
849 rtc::TimeMillis() - last_time_all_connections_removed_ >= timeout_delay_;
850 if (dead) {
851 Destroy();
852 }
853}

861 port_destroyed_callback_list_.Send(port);

864 RTC_DCHECK(network == network_);
865
866 UpdateNetworkCost();
867}

869std::string Port::ToString() const {
870 rtc::StringBuilder ss;
871 ss << "Port[" << rtc::ToHex(reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t>(this)) << ":"
872 << content_name_ << ":" << component_ << ":" << generation_ << ":" << type_
873 << ":" << network_->ToString() << "]";
874 return ss.Release();
875}

877// TODO(honghaiz): Make the network cost configurable from user setting.
878void Port::UpdateNetworkCost() {
879 uint16_t new_cost = network_->GetCost();
880 if (network_cost_ == new_cost) {
881 return;
882 }
883 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Network cost changed from " << network_cost_ << " to "
884 << new_cost
885 << ". Number of candidates created: " << candidates_.size()
886 << ". Number of connections created: "
887 << connections_.size();
888 network_cost_ = new_cost;
889 for (cricket::Candidate& candidate : candidates_) {
890 candidate.set_network_cost(network_cost_);
891 }
892 // Network cost change will affect the connection selection criteria.
893 // Signal the connection state change on each connection to force a
894 // re-sort in P2PTransportChannel.
895 for (const auto& kv : connections_) {
896 Connection* conn = kv.second;
897 conn->SignalStateChange(conn);
898 }
899}

901void Port::EnablePortPackets() {
902 enable_port_packets_ = true;
903}
904
905void Port::OnConnectionDestroyed(Connection* conn) {
906 AddressMap::iterator iter =
907 connections_.find(conn->remote_candidate().address());
908 RTC_DCHECK(iter != connections_.end());
909 connections_.erase(iter);
910 HandleConnectionDestroyed(conn);
911
912 // Ports time out after all connections fail if it is not marked as
913 // "keep alive until pruned."
914 // Note: If a new connection is added after this message is posted, but it
915 // fails and is removed before kPortTimeoutDelay, then this message will
916 // not cause the Port to be destroyed.
917 if (connections_.empty()) {
918 last_time_all_connections_removed_ = rtc::TimeMillis();
919 thread_->PostDelayed(RTC_FROM_HERE, timeout_delay_, this,
920 MSG_DESTROY_IF_DEAD);
921 }
922}
923
924void Port::Destroy() {
925 RTC_DCHECK(connections_.empty());
926 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << ToString() << ": Port deleted";
927 SendPortDestroyed(this);
928 delete this;
929}
